HEADWORD: Brehon
<hw>Bre"hon</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ir.
<ets>breitheamh</ets> judge.]</ety> <def>An ancient Irish or Scotch
judge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Brehon laws</b></col>, <cd>the ancient Irish laws, --
unwritten, like the common law of England. They were abolished by
statute of Edward III.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

